# About
**Lab:** Scoop to HDFS
**Objective:** Collect data with Scoop scripts into HDFS and into Hive
**File locations:** Cloudair DB in PostgreSQL
**Successful outcome:** Collect data with Scoop
**Before you begin:** Clooudair DB is in PostgreSQL
**Related lessons:** Sqoop in Action

---

paragraphs.text:
%md
# Setup

paragraphs.title: Ensure cloudair database is running in PostgreSQL
paragraphs.text:
%sh
export PGPASSWORD='BadPass%1'; psql -h db01.cloudair.lan -U devuser -d cloudair -p 5432  <<EOF
\dt
EOF

msg.data:
List of relations
 Schema |    Name     | Type  |  Owner  
--------+-------------+-------+---------
 public | eu_country  | table | devuser
 public | sale        | table | devuser
 public | us_customer | table | devuser
 public | ww_customer | table | devuser
(4 rows)

paragraphs.title: Delete HDFS /data/cloudair
paragraphs.text:
%sh
sudo -u hdfs hdfs dfs -rm -r -skipTrash /data/cloudair

%md
The message "Warning: /usr/hdp/3.1.5.0-152/accumulo does not exist! Accumulo imports will fail.""
should be ignored. To correct it you must install Accumulo.

# Solution

paragraphs.title: 1 - Scoop import table eu_countries into a target directory
paragraphs.text:
%sh
sudo -u hdfs hdfs dfs -rm -r -skipTrash /data/cloudair/eu_country
rm /home/zeppelin/eu_country.java

sqoop import \
--connect jdbc:postgresql://db01.cloudair.lan:5432/cloudair \
--username devuser \
--password BadPass%1 \
--table eu_country \
--target-dir /data/cloudair/eu_country \
--num-mappers 1

%md
Important: Ignore the warning about Accumulo, the code is not installed.

msg.data: Important: Ignore the warning about Accumulo, the code is not installed.

paragraphs.title: 2 - Check status of the Sqoop job
paragraphs.text:
%md
Go to Ambari
Open YARN Resource Manager web UI
Select Applications
Review Sqoop job

paragraphs.title: 3 - Check data in HDFS
paragraphs.text:
%sh
hdfs dfs -ls /data/cloudair/eu_country

paragraphs.title: 5 - Scoop import table sale by columns
paragraphs.text:
%sh
sudo -u hdfs hdfs dfs -rm -r -skipTrash /data/cloudair/sale
rm /home/zeppelin/sale.java

sqoop import \
--connect jdbc:postgresql://db01.cloudair.lan:5432/cloudair \
--username devuser \
--password BadPass%1 \
--table sale \
--columns "entry_date,item,first_name,last_name,city,country_name" \
--target-dir /data/cloudair/sale \
--num-mappers 1
